About SPX6900 (SPX)

SPX6900 (SPX) is a decentralized cryptocurrency, started in 2023 by an anonymous team. Compatible with the Ethereum network, SPX, pronounced Ess-Pee-Ex, is an ERC-20 token. Often referred to as a memecoin, SPX is a social cryptocurrency that pokes fun at the S&P 500 and traditional finance (TradFi) structures.
Fully decentralized, liquidity of the SPX token is locked for 69 years, with a value that is driven by community sentiment and speculative trading. As such, the price of SPX can fluctuate if holders buy or sell the token. SPX6900 was originally launched on Ethereum, with bridged versions of the token also available on Solana and Base.
Today, decentralized finance (DeFi) dapps are the most popular use for SPX6900. Holders of SPX are typically community-driven, memecoin traders.

  • How do I bridge SPX6900?

    Bridging crypto across chains allows you to move tokens from one network to another. With MetaMask, bridging SPX6900 (SPX) is easy, secure, and cost-effective. Our aggregator finds the most efficient routes to move your digital assets from one chain to another. And with cross-chain swapping, bridging and swapping can take place at the same time in a single transaction. Meaning: instead of bridging SPX from chain A and wrapping or unwrapping it on chain B, you can swap SPX from chain A to a second token on chain B, all in one move.
